# VulnScan v2.4 — Local AI Code Security Analysis

A **fully local** AI-powered code vulnerability scanner with a retro terminal UI.
Powered by **Qwen3** via **Ollama** — no internet required after setup.

---

## Quick Start

```bash
# 1. Install Ollama (if not already)
#    https://ollama.com

# 2. Clone / place this folder, then:
chmod +x run.sh
./run.sh
```

The script will:
- Check Ollama is installed and running
- Pull the `qwen3.5:9b` model if missing
- Set up a Python virtual environment
- Install Flask dependencies
- Launch the app at http://127.0.0.1:5000

---

## Manual Start

```bash
# Ensure Ollama is running with Qwen3
ollama serve &
ollama pull qwen3.5:9b    # if not already pulled

# Install Python deps
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Run
python app.py
```

---

## Features

| Feature | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Multi-file scan** | Upload an entire codebase folder |
| **Cross-file context** | Scanner sees how files relate |
| **Severity filter** | Critical / High / Medium / Low |
| **Fix generation** | Full corrected file + change log |
| **Integrity check** | Verifies fix doesn't break app logic |
| **Diff view** | Side-by-side original vs fixed |
| **One-click patch** | Write fix back to session file |
| **Download** | Grab patched files |

---

## Security Guardrails

- **Prompt injection detection** — files are scanned for override attempts before being sent to the LLM
- **Path traversal prevention** — all file operations are sandboxed to session directories
- **Rate limiting** — 10 requests per 60 seconds per IP
- **File type allowlist** — only source code extensions accepted
- **Binary rejection** — non-text files are refused
- **Size caps** — 500 KB per file, 50 MB total, 100 files max
- **No code execution** — purely static analysis
- **Security headers** — CSP, X-Frame-Options, etc.
- **Session isolation** — each browser session gets its own directory

---

## Supported File Types

`.py` `.js` `.ts` `.jsx` `.tsx` `.java` `.c` `.cpp` `.h` `.hpp` `.cs`
`.go` `.rs` `.php` `.rb` `.swift` `.kt` `.scala` `.sh` `.bash` `.sql`
`.html` `.css` `.json` `.yaml` `.yml` `.toml` `.env` `.cfg` `.conf` `.xml` `.tf` `.hcl`

---

## Adjusting the Model

Edit `core/scanner.py`:

```python
MODEL = "qwen3.5:9b"        
TIMEOUT = 300          # seconds per LLM call
```

For large codebases, increase `TIMEOUT` and use a larger model variant.

---

## Project Structure

```
vulnscan/
├── app.py              # Flask app, routes, security middleware
├── requirements.txt
├── run.sh              # Setup & launch script
├── core/
│   ├── scanner.py      # Ollama/Qwen3 interaction, prompts
│   ├── guardrails.py   # Prompt injection detection
│   └── file_manager.py # Safe file loading
├── templates/
│   └── index.html      # Retro terminal UI
├── uploads/            # Session file storage (auto-created)
└── outputs/            # Scan result JSON (auto-created)
```

---

## Notes

- The app binds to `127.0.0.1` only — not exposed to the network
- Each scan session is UUID-isolated; cleared on browser session end
- Scan times depend on Qwen3 model size and number of files
- `.bak` backups are created before any patch is applied